Jeanette Chabalala, News24Picture of dead rhino. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane &ndash; One white rhino was killed and another had to be put down after they were attacked by poachers at a farm in Rooiberg near Bela Bela, Limpopo police said on Sunday.Lt-Col Malesela Ledwaba said police were searching for five suspected poachers after the rhino were discovered on Saturday.One rhino was dehorned while the other one was shot but not dehorned, he said.&nbsp;"The second one was seriously injured and had to be put down."&nbsp;Two spent cartridges and one live round, possibly from a hunting rifle, were recovered at the scene.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.